76561198069159152,Recommended,298480,31572316,Posted: 5 May,all,wrb41977,"Decent game. Was looking for something similar to PTO (which is a hazy good memory), and this is... close enough I guess. No Alaska-class Battlecruisers, but whatever... Anyway, the game is a combat RTS dealing with naval warfare in World War II. There are three campaigns: Atlantic, Pacific, and Mediterranean. I have only done the Med campaign at this point, which allows you to choose between playing as the Brits or the Americans. It looks like you can choose to play as either of those in the other two campaigns, plus the Axis powers... which as it is an achievement to win those campaigns as the Germans or Japanese, I guess one should do that...Combat is somewhat easy to grasp, though at large numbers things slow down a bit, so leaving most to the computer might be advisable (which if you have a large enough force... well, you pretty much roll over EVERYTHING). The campaign I played was a bit annoying with the enclosed spaces and all, but became easier once I thinned the opposing forces down by taking their ports (which appears to be how you do that). Note: the higher rank ports will need a few battleships... not least because one or two tend to show up as defence...All in all, I would recommend it to anyone interested in such things.Update: Having now played the Atlantic and Pacific campaigns (from both sides), I will now add that the Med campaign seems the easiest. Now, the campaigns where you play as the Axis are the more difficult in their regions, and the Pacific campagins for both are by far the most difficult. This comes down to two factors. One is that the map changes (which to be fair, is probably necessary considering how much territory the Japanese have on the Allied Pacific map). The second is a little more direct. For the Allies, taking certain objectives can be hindered by the combo of fighting Shokaku-class carriers backed by Yamatos. Yamatos might be the most broken unit in the game. For the Japanese... well, your HQ can be sadistic. Seriously, I had them direct me to lead assaults on Hong Kong in the early game. So, I go okay, it's down to level 1, no big deal... and ran into the Brit's best battleship...Oh, and if you decide to attack the American ports in Hawaii? They are level 17s..."
