,Recommended,298480,11934702,"Posted: 31 August, 2014",all,golan,"If you are looking for a casual naval battle, this game is extremely gratifying. 2v2 (ships, not players), 3v3 battles are ok, you might even enjoy having one ship less in a confrontation.I write this review before being able to add carriers to my battlegroups on purpose, to give the entry level/casual player an idea of what to expect on first glimpse of the game.Pros:- good tutorials, comfortable learning curve, features many classes of WW2 era vessels;- manoeuvring matters, especially in destroyer/cruisers engagements;- simplistic aiming system, but functional and informative; it's what you'd expect in an arcadish game...-  extremely gratifying in small skirmishes, the tactical aspect of battles is covered sufficiently IMO;Some people complained about the AI. BS. It's what you'd expect of a game of this calibre, it won't impress you, won't win your battles for you, in balanced fights at least (during campaign, in some fights you can afford to let it do your fighting without worrying too much). But it does it's job, serves a good purpose. Will help you manage a large fleet, avoids collisions, keeps the enemy locked down, puts in some punches of its own, exactly where you need to increase the pressure. In the campaign, the level of a captain decides how well that vessel would perform.Cons:- idiotic story/campaign; didn't had any expectations, but there are plenty of objections that can be made about it;- controls are limited and in certain situations frustrating; there is no way to manage groups of ships or to move in formation;- camera positioning and control is limited and annoying;- you can't even decide how your group enters the battle, the ships position is randomised and extremely annoying; - outdated, you can now position your units, but it is still limited and annoying.- these issue makes strategy kind of irrelevant; big battles are rather frustrating;- poor graphics; I don't care about this matter that much, but graphics is quite poor by any standard.Overall, I can still appreciate this game. I recommend it because you'll have fun with it even with all its limitations."
