76561198332532440,Recommended,298480,32230716,Posted: 6 June,all,boris.glevrk,"First thing first: Good game, but a bit overpriced.If you are a WWII naval enthusiast who likes single player gaming and/or those famous WWII naval games just can't satisfy you, than you may very well give this game a try, just make sure you wait until it's on discount.For example, if you are unsatisfied about how they ""balance"" different ships in other games, like for instance WOWS, the modding functionality of this game can let you do it the way you want. Personally I spent my past 10 years looking for a game that gives back the rightful strength to aircraft carriers, and this game was the solution I found.Do note that the game features subpar graphics and sound quality, and some 3D models of ships are reversed (bow becoming stern and vise versa), combined with the price these are probably the only downsides of this game.For conclusion, this game is for WWII naval enthusiasts who fancy a more strategic playstyle (as opposed to a more action-packed, shooter-like playstyle in WoWS and the like)."
